  <body>
    <p><?oxy_comment_start author="kirkilj" timestamp="20200716T193226+0000" comment="On the feedback thread for this page, Radu mentioned that editor variables are also expanded when content is injected from a code templates or when a new file is created from a file templates.

Editor variables can also be referenced from the definition of another editor variable, as well as from Java or Javascript via the SDK API.

I think it would be helpful to include a list or table of all the contexts where an Editor Variable can be referenced as well as when it is evaluated. If a particular built-in variable is not available in some of these contexts, then it would be useful to see this summarized in a table."?>An
      editor variable is a shorthand notation for context-dependent information, such as a file or
      folder path, a time-stamp, or a date. It is used in the definition of a command (for example,
      the input URL of a transformation, the output file path of a transformation, or the command
      line of an external tool) to make a command or a parameter generic and re-usable with other
      input files. When the same command is applied to multiple files, the notation is expanded at
      the execution of the command so that the same command has different effects depending on the
      actual file.<?oxy_comment_end?></p>
